<div class="cz-newz-title-right-area">
<ul><li><a class="cz-news-report cz-comment-report-btn" href="#" title="Report" data-id="11046">&nbsp;</a></li>
<li><a class="cz-news-link" href="#cid11046" title="Link">&nbsp;</a></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
<p id="comment_html_11046" itemprop="commentText">"Grover explained that when plugged in, the cable is seen as a keyboard and a mouse. This means an attacker can input commands regardless of whether the device is locked or not."<br><br>
To clarify, this means that the device can interact with the lock screen in any way that an ordinary person could. This does NOT mean that the device can interact with the user session behind the lock screen.</p>
</div>
</div>
</li>
<li id="cid11048" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/UserComments">
<div class="cz-newz-comment-inner-wrappper  cz-second-comment">
